gov.nih.nlm.meme.xml
Interface XMLSerializer

All Known Implementing Classes:
MASRequestSerializer, ObjectXMLSerializer
public interface XMLSerializer

Generically represents a class that can convert objects to XML and back.

Author:
MEME Group

toXML

public String toXML(Object object)
             throws ReflectionException
This method generically converts an object to an XML document. The implementation should call toXML(Object,String) with a default indent value.

Parameters:
object - An object Object to serialize.
Returns:
An object String containing an XML representation of that document.
Throws:
ReflectionException - if conversion fails.

fromXML

public Object fromXML(String string,
                      boolean validating)
               throws ReflectionException,
                      XMLParseException
This method generically takes a file name, parses the file and produces a Java Object reprsented by that XML file. The parser used to parse the file is validating if the flag is true, and non-validating if false.

Parameters:
string - An object String representation of the file name of an XML file.
validating - A boolean representation of flag indicating whether or not the parser should validate.
Returns:
An object Object represented by the document in that file.
Throws:
ReflectionException - if conversion fails.
XMLParseException - if conversion fails.

                      boolean validating)
               throws ReflectionException,
                      XMLParseException
This method generically takes a Reader, parses it and produces a Java Object represented by the document in the Reader. The parser used to parse the file is validating if the flag is true, and non-validating if false.

Parameters:

validating - A boolean representation of flag indicating whether or not the parser should validate.
